```csharp
public async Task DeleteStockItemDiscardAsync(int brandId, string storeId, int itemId, int itemDiscardId)
{
    var discardItem = await dbContext.GetOrExceptStockItemDiscardAsync(brandId, storeId, itemId, itemDiscardId);
    dbContext.Remove(discardItem);
    await dbContext.SaveChangesAsync();
}
```

## **Critical Issue**: Orphaned Stock Movements

The current implementation **only removes the ItemDiscard** but doesn't handle the associated StockMovements. This will create **orphaned stock movement records** after we implement the stock movement creation feature.

## **Required Changes for Delete**

### **Option 1: Database Cascade Delete (Recommended)**
Set up cascade delete in the database schema so when ItemDiscard is deleted, related StockMovements are automatically removed:

```csharp
// In StockMovement entity configuration
modelBuilder.Entity<StockMovement>()
    .HasOne(sm => sm.ItemDiscard)
    .WithMany(id => id.StockMovements)
    .HasForeignKey(sm => sm.ItemDiscardId)
    .OnDelete(DeleteBehavior.Cascade); // This handles automatic cleanup
```

### **Option 2: Explicit Cleanup (More Control)**
Modify `DeleteStockItemDiscardAsync` to explicitly remove stock movements:

```csharp
public async Task DeleteStockItemDiscardAsync(int brandId, string storeId, int itemId, int itemDiscardId)
{
    var discardItem = await dbContext.GetOrExceptStockItemDiscardAsync(brandId, storeId, itemId, itemDiscardId);

    // Remove related stock movements first
    var relatedMovements = await dbContext.StockMovements
        .Where(sm => sm.ItemDiscardId == itemDiscardId)
        .ToListAsync();

    dbContext.StockMovements.RemoveRange(relatedMovements);
    dbContext.Remove(discardItem);

    await dbContext.SaveChangesAsync();
}
```

